</taxonomicName>
species group (see item Species Delimitation). Among all 
<taxonomicName id="49FB89E7FFEBFF8BE33CA34AB1CE322B" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Debilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE33CA34AB4953248" box="[1349,1436,1556,1580]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Debilos</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="49FB89E7FFEBFF8BE6AFA367B0563234" authorityName="Scherrer &amp; Aguiar" authorityYear="2012" box="[214,351,1592,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Debilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="makirum">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE6AFA367B1E33234" box="[214,234,1593,1616]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE685A366B0563234" box="[252,351,1592,1616]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">makirum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
along with 
<taxonomicName id="49FB89E7FFEBFF8BE789A367B3623234" authorityName="Scherrer &amp; Aguiar" authorityYear="2012" box="[496,619,1592,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Debilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="okarum">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE789A367B30D3234" box="[496,516,1593,1616]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE46FA366B3623234" box="[534,619,1592,1616]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">okarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="49FB89E7FFEBFF8BE404A367B201322B" authorityName="Scherrer &amp; Aguiar" authorityYear="2012" box="[637,776,1592,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Debilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="masipum">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE404A367B3983234" box="[637,657,1593,1616]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE4DAA366B201322B" box="[675,776,1592,1615]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">masipum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="49FB89E7FFEBFF8BE534A367B2D1322B" authorityName="Scherrer &amp; Aguiar" authorityYear="2012" box="[845,984,1592,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Debilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanimum">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE534A367B2683234" box="[845,865,1593,1616]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE50AA366B2D1322B" box="[883,984,1592,1615]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">sanimum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
uniquely have the mesoscutum with a medial, centro-posterior square dark mark. Nonetheless, 
<taxonomicName id="49FB89E7FFEBFF8BE551A303B2B93210" authorityName="Scherrer &amp; Aguiar" authorityYear="2012" box="[808,944,1628,1652]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Debilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="makirum">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE551A303B2353210" box="[808,828,1629,1652]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE534A302B2B93210" box="[845,944,1628,1652]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">makirum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be readily isolated from those by the combination of flagellomere 1 without whitish marks, fore and mid coxae, and hind t2 and t3 white, except dorsal brown mark taking fore coxa basal 0.5 and mid coxa basal 0.8, hind coxa dark brown, except apical margin whitish, and metasoma without yellowish parts. Otherwise, 
<taxonomicName id="49FB89E7FFEBFF8BE4A8A397B25F3284" authorityName="Scherrer &amp; Aguiar" authorityYear="2012" box="[721,854,1736,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Debilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="makirum">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE4A8A397B3EC3284" box="[721,741,1737,1760]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE48AA396B25F3284" box="[755,854,1736,1760]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">makirum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="49FB89E7FFEBFF8BE260A397B5873284" authorityName="Scherrer &amp; Aguiar" authorityYear="2012" box="[1049,1166,1736,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Debilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aserum">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE260A397B5243284" box="[1049,1069,1737,1760]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE242A397B5873284" box="[1083,1166,1737,1760]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">aserum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="49FB89E7FFEBFF8BE2BAA397B4343284" authorityName="Scherrer &amp; Aguiar" authorityYear="2012" box="[1219,1341,1736,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Debilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anokum">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE2BAA397B5DE3284" box="[1219,1239,1737,1760]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE29DA396B4343284" box="[1252,1341,1736,1760]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">anokum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of their coxae color pattern, but is separated from them by having the mesoscutum medially with centro-posterior square dark mark (
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE714A24FB08D334C" box="[365,388,1809,1832]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">vs</emphasis>
. without dark mark), propodeum anterior area moderately long, PLL 0.95 (
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE2A6A24FB5FF334C" box="[1247,1270,1809,1832]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">vs</emphasis>
. very long, 
<taxonomicName id="49FB89E7FFEBFF8BE3F8A24FB02A332F" authority="PLL" authorityName="PLL" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Debilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aserum">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE3F8A24FB49C334C" box="[1409,1429,1809,1832]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE6EEA26BB1E33328" box="[151,234,1845,1868]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">aserum</emphasis>
PLL
</taxonomicName>
1.30 and 
<taxonomicName id="49FB89E7FFEBFF8BE7EDA26BB340332F" authority="PLL" authorityName="PLL" box="[404,585,1844,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Debilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anokum">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE7EDA26BB0A13328" box="[404,424,1845,1868]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE7CFA26AB3063328" box="[438,527,1844,1868]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">anokum</emphasis>
PLL
</taxonomicName>
1.14), fore wing with two conspicuous dark spots (
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE2E9A26BB5AE3328" box="[1168,1191,1845,1868]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">vs</emphasis>
. with only one apical dark spot), and hind t2 and t3 entirely white (
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE4EBA207B3A03314" box="[658,681,1881,1904]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">vs</emphasis>
. t1 apical margin, t2–4 entirely white).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C6E1A1EFFFEBFF8BE6BEA222B03233DC" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8E44F264FFEBFF8BE6BEA222B03233DC" blockId="24.[151,1436,151,1976]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE6BEA222B04433F7" box="[199,333,1916,1940]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" reason="1">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE6BEA222B04F33F0" bold="true" box="[199,326,1916,1940]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Etymology</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
From the Carib word 
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFEBFF8BE433A222B39033F0" box="[586,665,1916,1940]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">mákari</emphasis>
, meaning “ankle,” in reference to the hind tarsomeres 2 and 3 white in this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
